LEPTOSPIROSIS - ECUADOR (02)
****************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Leptospirosis - Ecuador 980207100210
Date: Sat, 07 Feb 1998 18:39:24 -0300
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <luisjs@guttenberg.correionet.com.br>

According to El Mercurio (Internet edition, Feb 7), reports from Guayaquil
place the number of human leptospirosis cases at 20 (confirmed) in Guayas
and 6 possible cases in Manabi. Laboratory confirmation of serovars will
come - maybe next Monday - from CDC Puerto Rico, where the samples were
sent. Six patients died, only 3 have been confirmed as leptospirosis until
now.
According to the report, leptospirosis is usually seen as a rare disease in
Ecuador. Since 1984 when reporting began, the annual number of cases has
been around 10/yr.
The El Nino phenomenon is being held responsible for this outbreak, due to
intense heat and heavy rains. El Nino is also seen as responsible for 123
cases of malaria and 52 of dengue in Huaquillas, where insecticide spraying
has been going on since last Monday, Feb 6.
El Mercurio, as well as Internet editions of other newspapers, can be
accessed through:
<http://www.agestado.com.br>
This site has an excellent bookmarks page.
--
Luiz Jacintho da Silva. M.D.
