[2
Date: Sun, 8 Feb 1998 11:31:33 -0500 (EST)
From: Abramo Ottolenghi <ottolenghi.1@osu.edu>

According to press reports (El Comercio) the total cases of leptospirosis
in Ecuador has increased to 26 with 20 in the province of Guayas and 6 in
the province of Manabi. Of the 8 deaths ascribed to the disease only 3 had
been confirmed as due to leptospirosis. The other cases awaited
confirmation.
Authorities are surprised by the mortality seen and ascribe it to delays in
seeking treatment. The increase in cases (10/year is the usual incidence)
is ascribed to rats leaving flooded areas and entering [nearby homes. The
report further states that PAHO has recommended that rat eradication not be
carried out in flooded areas because of possible secondary consequences.
--
Abramo Ottolenghi
Professor Emeritus
